(256, 1, '2015-02-25 09:34:07', '2015-02-25 09:34:07', 'We all have the right to be doing what we are doing. We all want to be in charge of our own lives by making decisions, our own decisions of what we want to happen in our life.\r\n\r\nPutting yourself first is something that many women find very challenging to do. They often wonder why their lives are not fulfilled or inspiring like so many others seem to be. Putting yourself first is a very important and valid lesson for all of us. We are always worried about others, our family and friends and dont always know how to help them. We need to stop worrying and turn our attention back to ourselves and look at why we do the things we do.\r\n\r\nObviously, it feels good when we help someone else, however if its something we are doing constantly if can be detrimental to our health and wellbeing  we need to put ourselves high on our list of priorities. For some of us, the thought of being judged as selfish is reason enough to stop us from putting ourselves first.\r\n\r\nWomen need to understand that by making themselves a high priority they help others by being an example. The reason, is because we start to achieve goals and improve our self-esteem and our physiology changes  we walk tall with our heads held high. Our quality of life improves.\r\n\r\nSo how do we do this? We need to find our purpose our inner essence, our passion! We need to really look at ourselves and see what we are doing that is limiting us from growing spiritually. We all perceive our lives differently with different feelings, thoughts and visions. We need to connect to our inner being! Have you ever asked yourself the question What would you do if you had no fear? Im talking about the fear we hold onto, the fear that stops us discovering and understanding who we really are.\r\n\r\nNot being able to make decisions for you and think about what is best for you is very debilitating and depressing! If you feel this way why not give yourself the freedom and trust that only you can give to yourself. Only you know whats best for you. Maybe, you dont know where to start  you might even feel numb about your life or situation. The best thing to do is make that first decision instead of letting things just happen to you or turn out however they do. Just the first step of making a decision (even if youre not sure if its the right one) is a major step forward to putting yourself first!\r\n\r\nFor me, I found that meditation and mindfulness really helped. I was able to tap into my unconscious mind or if you prefer  your intuition or inner essence. Having some time to center yourself and find that quietness within you helps you connect to YOU. Its a wonderful feeling and one that you get better at each time you do it. Why not give it a go! Find that quiet and peaceful place and clear your mind. Of course it sounds easy and doesnt happen overnight but just keep practicing and it will happen. Then all you need to do is Listen, to you.', 'Putting Yourself First', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'putting-yourself-first', '', '', '2015-02-25 10:15:03', '2015-02-25 10:15:03', '', 0, 'http://localhost/sally-krivaci/?p=256', 0, 'post', '', 0),
